and velocity dispersion can be mostly attributed to two
fundamental correlations, one between b1 and α and the
other between α and the halo internal property. Considering
that there are relatively strong correlations between the mass
accretion rates Γmer, Γdif and the local environmental proxies
α and δ (see figures 8 and 9), it is interesting to ask (a) what
is the overall strength of assembly bias with mass accretion
rate in comparison to other internal halo properties, and (b)
what role, if any, do the local environmental proxies play in
explaining these trends?"
